United reached the semi-finals of the Capital One Cup last season, losing to Sunderland on penalties at Old Trafford. But having finished seventh in the Premier League and not qualified for Europe they are one of 13 Premier League clubs entering the draw at the second round stage.

Second round ties will take place on the week starting August 25. 

The last time United were in the second round draw was 1995, when they lost 4-3 on aggregate on York.  

Manchester United will be in a seeded team in Wednesday's Capital One Cup second-round draw, here is a list of teams they could potentially draw. 

Birmingham City, Bradford City, Brentford, Burton Albion, Charlton Athletic, Crawley Town, Crewe Alexandra, Doncaster Rovers, Gillingham, Huddersfield Town, Leyton Orient, Millwall, Milton Keynes Dons, Northampton Town, Oxford United, Port Vale, Portsmouth, Preston North End, Rotherham United, Scunthorpe United, Shrewsbury Town, Swindon Town, Walsall, Sheffield United or Mansfield Town, Sheffield Wednesday or Coventry City*

**If Coventry City beat Cardiff City, Sheffield Wednesday will be added to the seeded list.

 

